Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act
Minister of State for Child Care Expected Results
for the 2024-2025 Fiscal Year Regulation
Application of this regulation
1  This regulation applies to the Minister of State for Child Care for the 2024/2025 fiscal year.

Definition
2  In this regulation, "Act" means the Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act.

Minister of State for Child Care
3  The expected results that the Minister of State for Child Care is to achieve for the purposes of section 5 (3) of the Act are as follows:

(a)continue to implement initiatives that support ChildCareBC, the government's 10-year plan to provide universal, affordable, accessible, quality and inclusive child care to every family that wants or needs it;

(b)continue to engage with the following to inform the implementation of ChildCareBC and to guide the development of a distinctions-based approach to supporting Indigenous-led child care:

(i)all levels of government;

(ii)Indigenous governing bodies and other entities representing Indigenous peoples;

(iii)school boards, child care providers and other sector stakeholders;

(c)continue to monitor the implementation of bilateral agreements with the government of Canada;

(d)submit to Cabinet a report on the results referred to in paragraphs (a) to (c) on or before March 31, 2025.

[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act, S.B.C. 2001, c. 28, s. 9.]
